definitions.definition: The body of Jewish scripture comprising the Torah , the Neviim (prophets) and the Ketuvim (writings); corresponding to the Christian Old Testament (or roughly so, depending on the denomination ).

main_definition: ( biblical , Judaism ) The body of Jewish scripture comprising the Torah , the Neviim (prophets) and the Ketuvim (writings); corresponding to the Christian Old Testament (or roughly so, depending on the denomination ).
